The paper focuses on the design and evaluation of deep neural networks for image classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the importance of balancing accuracy, computational complexity, and network architecture complexity for on-device edge usage, which relates to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates a diverse set of deep convolutional neural networks, which involves comparing and analyzing large amounts of data, falling under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
